==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Bulbul
<hw>Bul"bul</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Per.]</ety>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>The Persian nightingale (<spn>Pycnonotus
jocosus</spn>). The name is also applied to several other Asiatic
singing birds, of the family <fam>Timaliid⟦ae⟧</fam>. The green bulbuls
belong to the <gen>Chloropsis</gen> and allied genera.</def>
<altsp>[Written also <asp>buhlbuhl</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Bulbule</ent>⟦br⟧
